==What is IRC?== Internet Relay Chat (IRC) is a form of real-time Internet chat or synchronous conferencing. It is mainly designed for group communication in discussion forums called channels, but also allows one-to-one communication via private message, as well as chat and data transfers via Direct Client-to-Client.
==Ways to get on IRC:== * [[Puredyne/Irssi |Use Irssi]] - popular terminal-based IRC client * [[Puredyne/XChat |Use XChat]] - graphical IRC client (not on the CD version - DVD/USB edition only) * web based client: [http://pjirc.goto10.org/?channel=puredyne http://pjirc.goto10.org/?channel=puredyne]
{{BookCat}}

