__NOTOC__
<noinclude><div class="noprint">{{print version|Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series/Print version||the Na’vi–English dictionary (glottal series)}}{{print version|Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/labial series/Print version||the Na’vi–English dictionary (labial series)}}{{print version|Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/velar series/Print version||the Na’vi–English dictionary (velar series)}}{{print version|Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/dental series/Print version||the Na’vi–English dictionary (dental series)}}{{print version|Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/nasals/Print version||the Na’vi–English dictionary (nasals)}}{{print version|Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/other consonants/Print version||the Na’vi–English dictionary (other consonants)}}</div>'''Table of Contents:''' [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#’|&nbsp;’]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#A|A]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#Ä|Ä]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/dental series#Ts (C)|C]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#E|E]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/labial series#F|F]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/nasals#Ng (G)|G]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/velar series#H|H]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#I|I]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#Ì|Ì]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/velar series#K|K]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/velar series#Kx|Kx]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/liquids#L|L]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/nasals#M|M]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/nasals#N|N]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/nasals#Ng (G)|Ng]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#O|O]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/labial series#P|P]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/labial series#Px|Px]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/liquids#R|R]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/dental series#S|S]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/dental series#T|T]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/dental series#Tx|Tx]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/dental series#Ts (C)|Ts]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/glottal series#U|U]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/other voiced#V|V]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/other voiced#W|W]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/other voiced#Y|Y]] [[Na'vi/Na'vi–English dictionary/other voiced#Z|Z]] </noinclude>

Confirmed Na’vi words and affixes are listed here in alphabetical order. ''Ä'', ''ì'', ''rr'', ''ll'', ''ng'' (= ''g''), ''ts'' (= ''c''), ''kx'', ''px'', ''tx'' are ordered as distinct letters from ''a'', ''i'', ''r'', ''l'', ''n'', ''t'', ''k'', ''p'', ''t''. Frommer's preferred orthography, with ''g'' for ''ng'' and ''c'' for ''ts'', is included in parentheses to allow electronic searches. Stress is indicated in [[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] transcription: The stress mark {{IPA|‹&nbsp;ˈ&nbsp;›}} appears ''before'' the stressed syllable, and syllable breaks are marked with a dot. Prefixes and adpositions which cause {{navi|Glossary|lenition}} are marked with a plus sign, ''ay+, −ro+''. Infix positions of verbs are marked in italics by ''•raised dots•''. Many of these are assumed rather than attested. Stem-changing words (short plurals, verbal contractions, genitives) are included; many short plurals are assumed rather than attested. 

Underlying {{IPA|/n/}} is spelled 'm' before 'p' in compound words, as in ''txampay'' (''txan-pay'') "sea". However, before 'k' it is spelled 'n', as in ''zenke'' (''zene-ke'') "not need to", despite the fact that it is pronounced {{IPA|/ŋ/}} and that this sound is spelled 'ng' before 'k' within a root such as ''pängkxo'' "chat". 

The vocabulary can be greatly expanded through productive use of Na’vi's word-building affixes, but such forms have not been included here unless they are attested in print or email from Paul Frommer. 

